cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a model for response selection in goal-oriented dialog systems. The paper focuses on using sequential matching models for multi-turn response selection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses neural networks for modeling, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also experiments with different architectures and techniques to improve the performance of the model, which makes cs.LG (Learning) another possible category. The paper also deals with information retrieval and ranking, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
